    "body": "## Problem\n\nExpense attendees can have `undefined` for their `email` field, which causes New Expensify to crash with \"Uh-oh, something went wrong!\" when rendering the affected report.\n\nThe crash occurs because `getPersonalDetailByEmail()` in `src/libs/PersonalDetailsUtils.ts` calls `email.toLowerCase()` without guarding against `undefined`. When `useReportPreviewSenderID.ts` iterates over transaction attendees and calls `getPersonalDetailByEmail(att.email)` with an attendee whose email is `undefined`, the app throws a `TypeError`.\n\n**Related internal issue:** Expensify/Expensify#618370\n\n## Crash Chain\n\n1. A transaction has an attendee object with `email: undefined` in `transaction.comment.attendees`\n2. `useReportPreviewSenderID.ts:72-77` iterates over attendees and calls `getPersonalDetailByEmail(att.email)`\n3. `getPersonalDetailByEmail` at `PersonalDetailsUtils.ts:143` executes `email.toLowerCase()` on `undefined`\n4. `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'toLowerCase')` → crash screen\n\n## Why This Happens\n\nThe `Attendee` TypeScript type (at `src/types/onyx/IOU.ts`) declares `email: string` (required), but Onyx data loaded from persistence/backend is not validated at runtime. Legacy data (e.g., attendees created through OldDot where only `displayName` was required) can have no `email` key at all, resulting in `undefined` at runtime.\n\n## Affected Code Locations\n\n| File | Line | Risk |\n|------|------|------|\n| `src/libs/PersonalDetailsUtils.ts` | 143-144 | **Crash origin** — `getPersonalDetailByEmail` calls `.toLowerCase()` on `undefined` |\n| `src/components/ReportActionAvatars/useReportPreviewSenderID.ts` | 72-77 | **High** — crash site calling `getPersonalDetailByEmail(att.email)` |\n| `src/pages/iou/request/MoneyRequestAttendeeSelector.tsx` | 91 | **High** — same unguarded `getPersonalDetailByEmail(attendee.email)` pattern |\n| `src/libs/OptionsListUtils/index.ts` | 2864 | **High** — processes `recentAttendees` from Onyx with same pattern |\n\n## Recommended Fix\n\nAdd a defensive guard in `getPersonalDetailByEmail` to handle `undefined`/empty email:\n\n```typescript\nfunction getPersonalDetailByEmail(email: string): PersonalDetails | undefined {\n    if (!email) {\n        return undefined;\n    }\n    return emailToPersonalDetailsCache[email.toLowerCase()];\n}\n```\n\nThis single change protects all 50+ callers across the codebase, including the 3 other vulnerable attendee-related call sites listed above. Several other callers already use `?? ''` to guard their input, but fixing it centrally is safer than patching each call site individually.\n\n\n<details><summary>Issue Owner</summary>Current Issue Owner: @jayeshmangwani</details>\n<details><summary>Upwork Automation - Do Not Edit</summary>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Upwork Job URL: https://www.upwork.com/jobs/~022039079611866537883</li>\n        <li>Upwork Job ID: 2039079611866537883</li>\n        <li>Last Price Increase: 2026-03-31</li>\n    </ul>\n</details>",
