    "body": "## Proposal: Optimize EmojiTrie Build Performance\n\n### Background\nThe app uses a custom prefix trie for emojis. This data-structure is used to enable fast autocomplete. The buildEmojisTrie is called on App startup, along with locale loading logic.\n\n### Problem\nWhen a user opens the emoji picker for the first time, the trie build blocks the JS thread longer than necessary. There are 4 inefficiencies we found:\n\nRecursive inserts with string copies: Trie.add recurses once per character and calls substring(1) at each level, allocating a new string on every step\nDouble trie traversal per keyword: Every keyword does a search to check if it exists, then a separate add or update — walking the same path twice\nSuggestions array rebuilt on every collision: When two emojis share a keyword, the entire suggestions array is recreated via spread rather than appended to\nQuadratic name-part allocation: getNameParts uses slice(index).join('_') for each suffix of the name, generating O(n²) intermediate arrays and strings\n\n\n### Solution\n\nIterative inserts: Rewrite Trie.add, search, and update to use index-based character access in a loop, eliminating all per-character string allocations\nSingle-pass getOrCreate: Add a method that walks to the end node once and returns {node, isNew}, replacing the search + add/update double traversal everywhere\nMutable suggestions: Initialize suggestions as a stable array and push/unshift into it directly. Since the normalized keyword node shares the same metadata object by reference, it stays in sync automatically — no extra update needed\nLinear name-part generation: Replace the map+slice+join in getNameParts with a single indexOf loop that appends suffixes directly with no intermediate allocations\n\n\nResults:\n\nWeb: 26ms - 16ms  (-38.4%)\niOS: 140ms - 95ms (-32.14%)\n\n<details><summary>Issue Owner</summary>Current Issue Owner: @shubham1206agra</details>\n<details><summary>Upwork Automation - Do Not Edit</summary>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Upwork Job URL: https://www.upwork.com/jobs/~022039022812847691682</li>\n        <li>Upwork Job ID: 2039022812847691682</li>\n        <li>Last Price Increase: 2026-03-31</li>\n    </ul>\n</details>",
